SIMPLE: tongue-tied
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tongue-tied
<hw>Tongue"-tied`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Destitute of the power of distinct articulation; having an
impediment in the speech, esp. when caused by a short fraenum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unable to speak freely, from whatever
cause.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Love, therefore, and <qex>tongue-tied</qex> simplicity.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tongueworm</ent>⟦br⟧
